{"ChunkNum": 0, "StartTime": 0.031, "EndTime": 183.249, "Content": "|0|:  The whole idea behind our programs are to involve community residents, community volunteers, make it as easy as possible for them to get involved in cleanup efforts and beautification projects. |1|: We have events going on throughout the city all year long, and I encourage anybody to check out our website, which is laocb.org. |2|: We have a calendar of events. |3|:  And people can just take a look and see what's going on in their neighborhoods and come out and enjoy the fun and make a difference in their neighborhoods. |4|:  Neighborhood events like Donuts and Coffee with the Deputy Chief are closing the gap between the perception of LA's police department and the reality. |5|: This kind of direct networking can help dispel some myths and build up community trust. |6|:  Right now, we're in front of a restaurant called 3030 Mexico, and we're just here to invite the community, right? |7|: We want the community to see us in a different light than actually at radio calls or stops. |8|: This is a restaurant where a lot of people patron to come and have breakfast, and we're just here to offer any questions and answers that people may want. |9|:  When we say community policing, it's events like Coffee with a Cop. |10|: It's us being out in the community, networking with our businesses, networking with folks that live and work in this community, and just sharing dialogue over a cup of coffee. |11|:  We're taking this as a great opportunity to engage with the public and close that gap and build that bridge between community member and also police officer and explain to them what it is that we do in regards with immigration and go ahead and brief them on our policy and at the same time to give them information. |12|: We have them in English and in Spanish, these booklets that states with the policy of the Los Angeles Police Department with respect to immigration. |13|: And we also have a QR code where that information can be downloaded on the cell phone. |14|:  you\n|15|:  The workers don't want to come to work because of the fear of being deported. |16|: We already have several workers who left. |17|: The people, the clients, don't want to come to eat because of the fear of being caught. |18|: It's a very sad, very difficult situation, both as business owners, as human beings, as Hispanic people. |19|:  LAPD's policy when it comes to immigration, so people are clear. |20|: We don't participate in civil immigration enforcement. |21|: One of the things that we like here is that people are coming in in their own environment. |22|: This isn't a radio call. |23|: This is an enforcement action.", "Embedding": [-0.0003585477, 0.00078595616, -0.017802058, -0.030908493, -0.0012754619, 0.037392236, 0.018617645, -0.037716575, 0.014611953, -0.03244226, 0.023667498, 0.019985955, 0.0034438483, 0.05936626, -0.017343419, 0.0116313165, -0.03486856, 0.006602894, -0.003325363, -0.0024257286, -0.008605269, 0.017972944, 0.11457966, 0.02213333, 0.030405313, -0.020240003, -0.025105324, 0.020807143, -0.035159975, -0.03172828, -0.06270231, -0.057375614, -0.036357157, -0.0074685654, -0.0012873259, 0.020262083, 0.02375546, 0.003139431, -0.01816492, -0.013793734, -0.004988843, 0.00314092, 0.016528184, 0.004913813, 0.03097453, 0.01029473, 0.0043499763, 0.0150523, -0.009228646, -0.015618209, 0.012174831, -0.0022754695, -0.03439862, -0.0060490677, -0.008238605, 0.04329123, 0.017612357, -0.008480611, -0.0027879134, -0.0046821763, 0.008739844, 0.018558143, -0.011892008, -0.013948288, -0.002970504, 0.00036654697, 0.021719981, -0.040183164, -0.013097006, 0.0005612725, 0.0038019805, 0.010219448, 0.015680688, 0.0025415143, -0.009110779, -0.018525874, -0.007945752, 0.0010174894, -0.0113175325, -0.008907874, 0.0034953703, 0.025243344, -0.023830831, -0.009331191, -0.004300186, 0.041585617, 0.031209676, -0.011013815, -0.025569301, 0.008420912, 0.008793392, -0.019877344, 0.021720933, 0.03642875, 0.003421