2, 0.023593877, -0.005429184, -0.034026485, -0.03422924, -0.02270301, 0.012508211, -0.0044539277, 0.008478282, 0.0089402525, 0.0045206617, -0.0200242, -0.035295334, 0.006109065, 0.00904677, 0.0077728527, 0.039471764, -0.0146482885, 0.008661813, 0.017675731, 0.023336211, 0.021202073, -0.023431066, 0.0047407625, 0.0023531793, 0.007969793, -0.0020583638, 0.017633319, 0.005473109, -0.0006897994, -0.009924333, -0.0155297825, -0.0063506817, -0.04691939, 0.02775798, 3.8637118e-05, -0.004907744, -0.05212525, 0.011923097, 0.04680229, -0.01369673, 0.0002940023, 0.018099453, -0.009785834, 0.016804518, -0.019867035, 0.018482227, 0.005106178, 0.013895679, 0.016932117, 0.019280728, -0.030467488, -0.009386921, -0.029143272, 0.001557689, -0.025572224, 0.0017012428, -0.00035888221, -0.020308126, -0.0019306773, -0.0073499107, -0.00010078395, 0.005382247, -0.012111229, -0.027767753, -0.024788115, -0.0028325245, 0.004784384]},
{"ChunkNum": 4, "StartTime": 477.494, "EndTime": 1034.378, "Content": "|66|: Because it's made for everyone. |67|: So we have both in-person and online programming too, depending on how people prefer\n|68|:  to access our resources. |69|: That's really important to us too, that it's not only in person, it's not only online. |70|: We're always looking to make our resources more available to more people. |71|:  The best place to go for more information is your local library, but also online, our website is lapl.org. |72|: And for littler ones, the website that has the children's resources is lapl.org slash kids path. |73|:  There's a new City of LA film industry liaison. |74|: September is National Preparedness Month. |75|: And the city attorney settles short-term rental and party house lawsuits. |76|: These stories up next on City Beat. |77|:  Mayor Karen Bass has announced her appointment of Steve Kang, president of LA City's Board of Public Works as the liaison to the film and television industry. |78|: According to Bass, Kang's deep knowledge of city's infrastructure and permitting will help improve local film processes and experiences for the entertainment industry. |79|: Kang is the official who oversees the city's contract with Film LA, balancing film industry needs with community impact. |80|:  Kang said filming is vital to the city's economy and city departments must prioritize their success. |81|: For more information, visit mayor.lacity.gov slash press. |82|:  September is National Preparedness Month, and LA City's Emergency Management Department has advice to follow if you haven't yet made an emergency plan. |83|: According to the department, steps include making a family emergency plan, building a kit, preparing for disasters, and teaching youth about preparedness. |84|:  Sign up for Notify LA to get city alerts or Ready LA County for emergency notifications across the greater Los Angeles area. |85|: LA City Emergency Management Department has disaster and emergency preparedness resources available online. |86|: For more information, visit emergency.lacity.gov. |87|:  LA city attorney, Heidi Feldstein Soto announced her office has settled lawsuits involving violations of the city's short-term rental and party house ordinances. |88|: Since late 2020, illegal short-term rentals were facilitated at one complex for over 3,000 nights, resulting in increased nuisance activity and complaints from neighbors. |89|: This housing falls under the LA rent stabilization ordinance, which bars it from the city's home sharing ordinance. |90|:  As part of the settlement, the litigants are to pay civil penalties and are prohibited from violating the home-sharing ordinance at any properties they manage or own. |91|: For more information, click the news tab at cityattorney.lacity.gov. |92|:  The Department of Cultural Affairs runs art centers throughout Los Angeles. |93|: But wait, there's more. |94|: They also support three multidisciplinary artists who connect even more directly with the communities, bringing ideas to life through art. |95|:  What is the outreach and engagement for DCA? |96|: Community Arts has been active for a long time with our art centers all across Los Angeles. |97|: Community engagement has been, I would say, augmented by our community engagement outreach team. |98|: We have three art instructors. |99|: They are amazing, talented, creative, multidisciplinary artists who go out into the community and are providing true, meaningful arts activities with the community. |100|:  What inspired me to become a teaching artist for DCA was number one, their mission. |101|: I loved DCA's mission as far as giving back to my community. |102|: I love the idea of spreading out, going throughout LA and going to all the different communities and giving them opportunities, grants, all sorts of amazing things that we offer. |103|: It really aligned with my morals as an artist. |104|:  When I heard about DCA and I saw the opportunity of them having this outreach team that was going straight to the community, it felt like a perfect place for me to give back and to share what art is to me. |105|: But I like to think that me as a person, I can be an example. |106|: You know, I'd rather be an example more than an impact, I suppose. |107|:  And what I mean by that is like, while I'm working with the community, while I'm teaching, while I'm talking, sharing ideas, exploring ideas through the medium of art, I like to think that maybe somewhere out there, like while I'm working on the field, I'm able to interact with somebody and that me being an example to them opens up their mind to like other possibilities in their lives and in their communities. |108|:  As we know, Los Angeles is huge, and a lot of folks do not have that access, and so we really want to make sure that we're bringing that arts access as far-reaching as possible to as many people as possible. |109|: Regardless of age, background, we're really trying to have people participate in activities that they might not be used to, that might be interesting and engaging for them, getting people to think about the arts in different ways, and just bringing it to as many people as we can. |110|:  The library is so much more than a building. |111|: It's a community hub. |112|: So when the Venice Branch Library is celebrating 30 years, they feature the 30 community members who've helped the Venice Branch become the unique place it is today. |113|: We are here at the Venice Branch Library and we are celebrating the 30th anniversary of this beautiful branch library, this beautiful building. |114|:  This library is such a hub to the community. |115|: We wanted to honor a lot of people in the Venice community who've kind of made this place what it is. |116|: We selected 30 of the most influential people for the Venice 30th. |117|: And we've had several people from this poster. |118|: They are here today to help us celebrate. |119|: And it's been a wonderful day of celebration. |120|: We have Bea Coleman unveiling of her artwork, which is in the children's section. |121|: We're doing swing dancing. |122|: We're doing a zine program today. |123|:  It brings in an incredibly diverse population. |124|: You know, people who really need the services and then people who like a little extra. |125|: The extra is also where the Friends of the Venice Library come in because we fund, I'd say about 98% of the programs that happen at the library. |126|:  This is much more than just a place to go to get your book or to be on the computer for a bit. |127|: This is a real community place and it is an honor to serve it and honor the people who serve the community. |128|:  I think what we're really celebrating are the people, the people in this community who have benefited from this library all of these years, the incredible city staff who work for the library department and the LA Public Library who provide outstanding service at this library, and all of the lives that are changed, whether it's a young person who develops a lifelong love of reading by coming to story times and craft programs here at this library, whether it's a senior that comes to a book club here. |129|:  or someone who comes to explore our collections and just make use of this incredible space. |130|: To our wonderful friends of the library who are signing new members up today and who are providing extra treats for a reception and it's just a very celebratory day and it's a reminder of how important libraries are. |131|:  From the neighborhood block where it began to a city rooftop, the Leimert Park Jazz Festival is now in its sixth year. |132|: While rooted in the black cultural hub of Leimert Park, the festival encompasses the best jazz in the country. |133|:  We are at Lamarque Park Jazz Festival. |134|: It's their sixth annual jazz festival. |135|: It started in a neighborhood. |136|: And look what it's grown to. |137|: We're right here at Baldwin Crenshaw Plaza, upstairs on the parking lot. |138|: It's been transformed into a festival with folks that are selling hats and rings, earrings, clothes. |139|: And we also have all these food vendors. |140|: It is really wonderful.", "Embedding": [-0.00059502875, 0.014922084, -0.042637005, 0.020056168, -0.0025930514, 0.04696348, 0.038630985, -0.03358924, 0.0013707652, -0.027579524, 0.02529449, 0.013822913, 0.0027673906, 0.006292491, 0.004230452, -0.013889727, -0.023369748, -0.028271608, -0.029084831, -0.0050305543, -0.00028676252, 0.013078417, 0.10555291, 0.00058853434, 0.022708816, -0.028574876, -0.027817382, -0.004214878, -0.04826644, -0.029511593, -0.07546287, -0.013369747, 6.376885e-05, -0.018951692, -0.0037994925, -0.00590095, 0.0010355787, 0.0040528513, -0.031004125, 0.004666929, 0.011499824, 0.02349136, 0.01568568, 0.002997693, 0.008947399, 0.007864846, 0.0050923037, -0.004382562, -0.026360093, -0.02306808, 0.01042153, -0.0015970707, -0.024755515, -0.022875989, 0.01623796, 0.051676087, 0.017657382, -0.007035671, 0.00755297, -0.0050755804, 0.0031302257, 0.015364717, 0.01831491, -0.0122287795, -0.00030400444, -0.009317357, 0.00536047, -0.014716642, -0.0018539887, -0.014442314, 0.010507641, -0.027876489, -0.0014388635, -0.02051261, 0.0037994517, -0.017509928, -0.011634128, 0.01188764, 0.015686493, 0.018355535, -0.002927744, 0.023858536, -0.004090219, -0.0048620077, -0.020096688, -0.0049673794, 0.029784923, -0.004147846, -0.00955481, 0.0054898993, 0.008981129, -0.049996536, 0.01452181, -0.001134986, 0.011369371, 0.009223509, -0.006021077, -0.027471596, 0.010633571, 0.0018441952, 0.0049234456, -0.044986825, 0.023683485, -0.0037739056, -0.0141072115, -0.017357016, 0.01141723, -0.013526199, 0.012902381, 0.011902373, 0.017964402, -0.00020163044, -0.030905753, -0.022747524, 0.007452668, -0.0071727475, 0.0117844725, -0.017496161, 0.001659651, 0.029071288, -0.0026356291, 0.0073475153, 0.008983685, 0.0033017744, 0.0068758484, -0.06303007, -0.009593215, -0.013116184, 0.038317505, 