{"ChunkNum": 6, "StartTime": 1107.343, "EndTime": 1407.544, "Content": "|151|: Well, every year it gets bigger and bigger. |152|: But what it does is it anchors our community as one of the jazz centers, not just in Southern California and California, but in the country. |153|:  This is the black cultural hub of Los Angeles, the Merc Park, and that's what they'll walk away knowing for sure. |154|: That black asphalt lives here. |155|:  Shutting down Los Angeles and Main Street in the heart of downtown isn't normally a cause for celebration. |156|: But when it comes to a classic car show, El Pueblo got some traffic stopping models and celebrated the pride of lowrider culture. |157|:  We're happy to have the third annual El Pueblo de Los Angeles car show here at El Pueblo Historical Monument. |158|: We're really lucky to have this for the third year where we shut down Los Angeles and mainstream here in the heart of downtown LA to have show cars on display. |159|: For us, it's more like a religion. |160|: You know, we like to bring the Chicano style back to Los Angeles and especially Olvera Street. |161|:  It is an art and it's very difficult. |162|: It takes thousands and thousands of dollars to keep these cars to look original and classic and original look. |163|: The motivation more it's just for the young generation you know they love coming out here seeing the cars and one day they're going to want to build the car themselves or we just hand our cars down to our kids. |164|:  They love it. |165|: I loved it growing up as a kid too, watching my dad driving his lowrider. |166|:  El Pueblo is really special because we always pride ourselves on having our museums free and also most of our programming free as well. |167|: So having the third annual car show just shows support to the community and to draw more visitors in to celebrate the history of Los Angeles and low-riding culture. |168|: An LA car show wouldn't be complete without going low and slow with the low riders. |169|:  LA City's Department of Aging is on the ball with a new program in conjunction with the Los Angeles Sparks. |170|: The women's basketball team and the department got together to take a senior to the game. |171|: And the result? |172|: Well, it's a win-win. |173|:  Taking seniors to a game is our first initiative. |174|: We're working with the Department of Aging. |175|: The game is just the first step, but we will be out visiting the seniors at their facility and just giving them an opportunity just to have some fun and to be on the move. |176|: When the seniors found out about it, they were super excited to have a night out and enjoy this WNBA game. |177|: So we're really excited. |178|:  for the Department of Agents to put on an event like this, it really means a lot to us. |179|: They always take us on different events, and now we're here at the Crypto.com to see this work, and they're gonna give us a win. |180|: I'm very, very excited. |181|: I can't wait for the game to start, to be jumping up and down for the spotters. |182|:  Obviously, these are the benefactors, right? |183|: Our older adults, they need to know that we're a very active community. |184|: We get involved in all sorts of community events, and they love to have a lot of fun. |185|: It's not just sitting around playing games and stuff all day. |186|: We like to get out and move. |187|:  This keeps us active, so we don't want to be sitting at home, you know, maybe watching TV or whatever. |188|: Them providing outside activities for us is great for us because, you know, we don't want to just be sitting around. |189|: These are our golden years and we would like to keep them golden, exactly, and very active. |190|:  We are fighting for a playoff spot. |191|: So I hope they are ready to cheer loud. |192|: I hope they're ready to catch some t-shirts, but we're gonna spotlight them. |193|: So the Department of Aging is our community spotlight for tonight. |194|: We will put the camera on them in their seats, you know, just catch them having fun. |195|: It just shows how the Los Angeles Squires and the Department of Aging, how we're bringing the community together. |196|: No matter the age, you know, everybody can have fun.", "Embedding": [-0.0004885267, -0.027875347, -0.018168071, 0.0041656066, -0.002177133, 0.0567094, 0.036090687, -0.0092709195, 0.012097602, -0.018470364, -0.0061502066, 0.05314437, 0.003941099, 0.0039977767, -0.04350006, 0.009681993, -0.060973793, -0.040940214, -0.012791314, -0.00085301587, -0.00682421, 0.015175187, 0.035138868, 0.0008167474, 0.046472088, -0.06960604, -0.026419874, 0.025660746, -0.01072004, -0.023890723, -0.06634785, -0.038905635, 0.006415587, -0.034434523, -0.0013777039, 0.018472178, 0.032514147, -0.0020317798, 0.01913443, 0.0011688127, -3.8277216e-05, 0.012674344, 0.013233913, 0.007813664, 0.0138492035, 0.000643048, 0.006135965, 0.00041907193, -0.0025030037, -0.011565603, 0.011643796, -0.015178294, -0.010616681, -0.008337925, -0.050167773, 0.07322615, 0.0067940154, 0.0010786449, 0.015121561, -0.023341447, 0.0028388593, -0.0048071127, -0.014246964, -0.017791077, -0.007653517, -0.008418049, 0.006482501, 0.0033988683, -0.0058085904, -0.016196577, -0.034525774, 0.0060806694, -0.03474338, -0.024193635, 0.009180229, -0.011181375, -0.005970384, 0.0013216435, 0.010155744, 0.0028449476, -0.02228637, -0.0036584164, 0.0009116527, -0.013842748, -0.0074421177, 0.02895605, 0.02700045, 0.00086763874, 0.014871957, 0.0015283473, 0.012719405, -0.04401479, 0.008611495, 0.0038540538, -0.0049564335, 0.0029356147, -0.026467642, -0.009688642, 0.018090293, -0.0003146762, 0.0013502688, -0.0077653923, 0.017126147, -0.0044720345, 0.0037937097, -0.014893217, 0.0110414205, -0.018939799, -0.005513949, 0.011280703, 0.014103904, 0.002205212, 0.019578448, -0.007018772, 0.009981496, -0.002204877, 0.014326789, -0.0045853937, -0.0018906061, -0.059914198, 0.0021836893, 0.011088795, 0.008351116, -0.011123755, 0.0051218104, 0.0049312427, -0.007991928, 