{"ChunkNum": 11, "StartTime": 2771.264, "EndTime": 2880.34, "Content": "|278|: All right. |279|: All right, this morning, folks, I have a great opportunity to honor the Lanark Dragons walking soccer team. |280|: Now, a lot of times we come to this podium with high school champions, sometimes professional athletes, but what we're often missing is our senior athletes. |281|:  And before I go any further, when I talk about walking soccer, I want you to understand what I'm talking about. |282|: So before I continue, I'd like ITA to roll a clip. |283|: So we are in Kenoga Park at Lanark Recreation Center, and we have our Walking Soccer World Cup today. |284|: Play ball. |285|:  So the intention behind creating the World Cup, they play every single Wednesday and Friday here. |286|: So they train twice a week. |287|: Each year we do a culminating event where they get together with their countrymen and play against one another in a tournament and they end up with awards. |288|: So it's a really fun thing that helps the program grow because they have something to look forward to at the end of each year. |289|:  So we have six teams here. |290|: We have United States, we have Israel, we have Peru, South America, England, and Ukraine. |291|: All the players were born or have citizenship of the country that they have. |292|:  And it's like being a kid. |293|: It's like being 70 years old. |294|: We're 70 and up. |295|: I have two players that one is 86 and the other one is 84. |296|: And on the other place we have one that is 94 years old and he's still playing. |297|: So that is encouraging, isn't it?", "Embedding": [-0.00061264, 0.021824727, 0.001455578, -0.027667297, -0.00218868, 0.050521392, 0.05436912, -0.00025017728, -0.010292841, -0.030549778, 0.02627534, 0.0037701107, 0.00083110156, -0.013397164, -0.027629348, -0.0035325065, 0.0058552627, -0.03683326, -0.041221246, 0.0040867217, 0.004681843, 0.006960446, -0.004882638, 0.026172273, 0.009483131, -0.06671477, -0.020542342,