{"ChunkNum": 13, "StartTime": 2964.925, "EndTime": 3322.097, "Content": "|314|: Alright. |315|:  So walking soccer was a concept that Dr. Ben Drillings, who witnessed this sport being played outside of the city of Los Angeles, he decided, I want to bring this to Los Angeles. |316|: And not just to Los Angeles, but to the West Valley, not just to the West Valley, but specifically to Lanark Park in Canoga Park. |317|: Dr. Drillings, who was a lifelong soccer player, was unable to continue to participate in traditional soccer due to some injuries. |318|:  But he craved that spark that he once had, which he loved so much when he was playing the sport. |319|: So approximately three years ago, Dr. Drilling's figured out a solution. |320|:  He established a league for individuals age 60 and above with teams organized by nationality or ethnic background. |321|: And the sport has just gone gangbusters. |322|: It's gained popularity among seniors who maintain active lifestyles but either can't or don't want to continue to compete in the way that they used to. |323|: One great thing about this league is, as I understand it, injuries are very rare. |324|:  This year, the Lanark walking soccer team represented Team USA in the Walking Soccer World Cup in Mallorca, Spain. |325|: And as I said, we bring up champions here. |326|: Well, these guys represented LA in Spain for the United States, and they achieved a remarkable fourth place finish. |327|: So let's hear it for the Lanark Dragons. |328|:  So next I'd like to introduce Lanark Park director, Jeremy Aldridge, who was here a few months ago, has been here a number of times, but often it's with the young champions that he's coming here. |329|: So today he's here with some older champions, but he does such a bang-up job in Lanark Park. |330|: I can't tell you how he's turned that place around. |331|: I'm so proud, Jeremy, of the work that you've done there and continue to do there. |332|: So without further ado, Jeremy Aldridge. |333|:  Thank you so much Bob, we really appreciate your support and it's only really through your support and the city council's support that our Department of Recreation and Parks continues to help make Los Angeles the great city that it is. |334|:  About three years ago, Ben literally came in off the street and sat down with his energy and with his commitment and passion and convinced me that we could do this program together. |335|: So it was a great day meeting him. |336|: I'm so proud of this program and of this group of seniors for what they've done and what we're accomplishing at the park. |337|:  So along with Bob, I'd really like to thank Ben for bringing the idea. |338|: I really said yes, and then we've had a very good partnership since then. |339|: So I'm just gonna step aside and let Ben talk about the program. |340|: Thank you so much for having us. |341|: We always come here with gratitude for your support. |342|: Thank you. |343|: Thank you. |344|: Good morning, city council members. |345|:  My name is Dr. Ben Drillings. |346|: I'm a chiropractor and a former professional soccer player. |347|: After a career-ending injury, I spent decades searching for a way to get back to the field in a safe, sustainable way. |348|: Three years ago, I created the walking soccer, a simple, low-impact version of the game I love for players ages 60 to 85. |349|:  There is no running, no tackling, and no high contact. |350|: We have removed barriers so all the adults and those returning to activity can play safely. |351|:  What began in just four people has grown to over 100 participants across three locations. |352|: We have organized community-based World Cup events that celebrate the diversity of our neighborhoods. |353|: And we are preparing for another one this November. |354|:  Walking soccer promotes exercise balance and overall physical health. |355|: It also brings meaningful social connection among the players, supporting mental well-being. |356|:  With both the World Cup and the Olympics coming to Los Angeles, this is the perfect moment for our city to lead. |357|: I'm asking the Council to adopt a city-wide walking soccer initiative, designate fields, promote programs in our parks, and help publicize city-sponsored walking soccer leagues. |358|: The infrastructure is already here. |359|: We just need your support. |360|:  I'm ready to coordinate training, organize volunteers, and help launch these programs before the World Cup. |361|: Let Los Angeles be the first major city to embrace walking soccer. |362|: Now, it's very important, before I close, I want sincerely to thank Jeremy, who runs the Lanark Recreation Park in Kanoga Park, for believing in this project from the beginning. |363|: Thank you, Jeremy. |364|:  And now I want to bring Dov and Rachel here. |365|: Come on second. |366|: Can you please hold it for them? |367|: Dov and his wife, Rachel, who keeps things moving on the ground, we could not have done it without your help. |368|: We could not have done it without your help. |369|: Thank you. |370|: And thank you for all the players. |371|:  that took time and came here today. |372|: And thank you for everyone. |373|: All right.", "Embedding": [-0.00055325375, 0.013207027, -0.020231485, -0.019606678, -0.0020052472, 0.09196907, 0.053678364, 0.039305646, -0.0115293935, -0.057442926, 0.016239017, 0.03155745, 0.0024727716, 0.005139367, -0.028673178, -0.011873964, -0.013789245, -0.020724617, -0.011967844, 0.0011797209, -0.004981489, -0.007721935, 0.00979141, 0.0033406839, 0.026427722, -0.029963635, -0.020229975, -0.008254607, -0.013199795, 0.052264486, -0.06564122, 0.013900377, 0.014598456, -0.01321735, -0.0024553614, 0.018676432, 0.0046953796, 0.002361376, -0.022768755, -0.0013709986, -0.00041743377, 0.011338615, -2.0640418e-05, 0.010831111, 0.010354939, 0.024141282, 0.0028476461, -0.014721605, 0.015637556, -0.009412529, 0.010563697, 0.0020675287, 0.01682259, -0.015809253, -0.0070879348, 0.0064687296, 0.027084