{"ChunkNum": 22, "StartTime": 3554.293, "EndTime": 3799.168, "Content": "President. |434|: Colleagues, we have a lot to celebrate today, and I'm just so honored that we're celebrating the contributions of a real shero in our community, Veronica Lewis. |435|: She has been with Hoppix for the past 21 years, providing exemplary services to our community and to the city of Los Angeles, helping to eradicate homelessness. |436|:  HOPX, as you know, stands for Homeless Outreach Program Integrated Care Services, and that exactly is what has occurred. |437|: After over 21 years of service, 14 years of which she's been as director of HOPX, Ms. Lewis is stepping down while moving on to other\n|438|:  her next journey. |439|: This departure marks the closing of a fun chapter. |440|: And while Veronica's time is coming to an end at Hoppix, her legacy will not be forgotten. |441|: Veronica is a pillar in the South LA community, her commitment to advocating for vulnerable populations, courage to speak out for what is right, and the dedication to equity and throughout all of her work is admirable. |442|:  Over the course of her tenure, Veronica has simplified, solidified relationships with strategic partners to further Hoppock's mission, served as a mentor to many future local leaders, and empowered her team to think outside the box and problem solve with a burst people approach. |443|: Veronica's impact on the CD9 will be felt for decades to come. |444|: Her passion for housing, mental health,\n|445|:  substance abuse recovery and reentry services for unhoused folks is unmatched and unwavering. |446|: To know Veronica is to know someone who never wavers in her commitment to doing what's right and to doing what's just. |447|: So Veronica, we applaud your efforts, your decades of hard work and the lasting influence that you've had over the city of LA and specifically in CD9. |448|:  No matter where you go next, we know that those around you are going to be lucky to have your guidance, your encouragement, and your support. |449|: Now, let me just ask someone to come forward who knows Veronica very, very well and who has been responsible for her guidance and development, Joyce Kelly, her mom. |450|:  Good morning. |451|: It's really an honor and a blessing to be here. |452|: Thank you so much for honoring my daughter, Veronica Lewis, and having had the privilege of watching her grow and develop. |453|: I think there's some important things that you need to know about Veronica's history. |454|:  As a young child, her father made sure that she and her brother attended community coalition meetings, at which time Karen Bass was just getting her start. |455|: So she's always had a passion. |456|: Being born and raised in South Central Los Angeles, she was always very observant of the needs of her people. |457|:  So I had the opportunity to watch her career bloom over the years as she grew at Hoppix and I tell you honestly a lot of times we say things but the passion that this young lady has to help is unsurpassed. |458|:  So I want to thank the council for recognizing her, but I also have to point out that while we're recognizing Veronica, the efficacy of which she achieved her excellence could not have been done without a lot of the support of our council members who she didn't mind getting in their ear. |459|: And then we also have a wonderful advocate here that they have collaborated. |460|: So just know that there are people that genuinely care. |461|: And again, thank you for honoring my baby. |462|:  Veronica Darnell Lewis.", "Embedding": [-0.00053815386, 0.018708406, 0.00089956506, 0.0063496665, -0.0021745632, 0.06117001, 0.052531555, 0.0482736, -0.008275821, 0.019825542, 0.038719397, 0.020174585, 0.003213049, -0.008306553, -0.007749256, 0.025458885, -0.0078932885, -0.011225399, -0.0275798, 0.0026901376, 0.0063648103, -0.004832809, 0.13947007, 0.017472759, -0.0040982175, -0.023692233, -0.017452337, 0.02050425, 0.013204732, -0.001084852, -0.059