004934968, 0.002991891, 0.007848779, 0.0018607008, -0.00553784, 0.0041307556, 0.014790548, -0.018819893, -0.015852736, 0.01322021, 0.0065216245, 0.0016439856, -0.020859424, 0.008412476, 0.027136195, 0.030763647, -0.014627772, 0.02039362, -0.0091179265, -0.012048554, 0.0018619269, -0.029744156, 0.013603152, -0.0010765487, -0.006947544, 0.021117983, -0.021482617, 0.045414235, 0.0068019778, -0.008410011, -0.005709116, -0.00321151, -0.03088412, -0.0062233163, -0.009932918, 0.019339018, -0.03358069, 0.0062645776, -0.0135332765, 0.0086048795, 0.013517251, -0.01476184, -0.00088075333, 0.015273728, -0.007450765, -0.0015359205, 0.02535529, -0.02055414, -0.0039057683, -0.009114621, 0.016264247, 0.017089985, 0.033201985, 0.026763238, 0.0037582165, 0.020692987, -0.0054490073, -0.027148236, -0.011276718, 0.00090977084, -0.0072955033, -0.0355836, -0.045160767, 0.019188017, 0.00447194, -0.0051625962, -0.008772676, -0.024376359, -0.011951985, 0.020010669, 0.00085497624, -0.0333398, -0.027163075, -0.00062510144, 0.03174653, -0.006963791]},
{"ChunkNum": 26, "StartTime": 4199.93, "EndTime": 4552.936, "Content": "President. |524|: Veronica. |525|: I certainly appreciate the work that you've done in our community for all of these years. |526|: I think that not only council members, but people in 8, 9, 10, and 15 are going to look for you because you have left a lasting impression\n|527|:  on everybody in these last 21 years. |528|: It is amazing that you gave so much of yourself to make better lives for other people. |529|: And I can't tell you how important that is. |530|: What a beautiful spirit. |531|: Your mother talked about how great of a daughter you are, but what a beautiful spirit you have. |532|: We're gonna miss you at Hoppix, but we gonna find you wherever you are. |533|:  And really get your advice on how to make a difference in our homeless community. |534|: Thank you so much for all your time and energy that you have given to this space. |535|: And I wish you well on the next part of your journey. |536|: Thank you. |537|: Thank you, Councilmember Price, for giving us the opportunity to give her flowers. |538|: Thank you. |539|:  Thank you, Councilmember Price, for bringing this wonderful woman in to be honored today. |540|: And I want to thank you for your work and your words. |541|: And I wanted to, particularly for your mother, the amount of emotion and pride that you've given your mom and all of your friends and family, the outpouring of emotion says everything about your commitment, your passion, and your work. |542|:  And if there's anything that makes a community proud, it's to see someone excel in a role that they're very passionate about. |543|: So I want to thank you for dedicating your life to this important work for being of service to our community. |544|: We know that the work continues where I'm certain\n|545|:  You don't just walk away from something like this. |546|: So I'm certain there's probably more on the horizon in your advocacy. |547|: But thank you for your service to our city, for the work and the imprint that you leave behind. |548|: It's going to continue. |549|: But again, I just taken by the amount of\n|550|:  of a motion this morning. |551|: It really does, in a moment like this when our communities, so many of our communities are suffering, it's a reminder how one person can in fact make a difference. |552|: So I just wanted to say thank you for your service. |553|:  Thank you, Council President. |554|: Thank you, Council Member Price, for bringing in Veronica and honoring her for all the work that she's done in this city, but not only the city, the county of Los Angeles. |555|: Your work has impacted 10 million people, and we haven't done a lot of work together since I've come into office, but the decade before I came into office, we've been working together, from LARP to Measure J to Care First Community Investments. |556|:  We've been there. |557|: You've been changing the systems. |558|: You've been making the county work better to serve our communities and not leave people behind. |559|: What you said here today, the humanity of people, that is what has got us to this point where we invest more in some of these programs that keep our people alive. |560|: Where before, the conversation was, why even invest in harm reduction? |561|: Why even invest in these people? |562|: And you've been in it since then, and you've gotten us to this point. |563|:  where we do more recognize the humanity of our community members. |564|: And that helps us save lives. |565|: So I'm grateful for everything you've done. |566|: I'm looking forward to where you're taking your energy, your leadership, the way you problem solve, and the way, again, you bring people with you. |567|: Don't hesitate to lean on us. |568|: But I'm just very grateful for all the effort that you've put into the millions of people here in the city of Los Angeles and the county of Los Angeles. |569|: Thank you so much for your work. |570|: Thank you. |571|: Thank you so much, Councilmember. |572|: Councilmember McCosker. |573|:  Veronica, for all of your work, people know that we call ourselves the one five. |574|: And one of the greatest inspirations for the one five is one of our five communities is the beloved community of Watts, often overlooked. |575|: We remind ourselves every day we're the one fives. |576|: We don't overlook a community. |577|: Within the community of Watts, who's the most overlooked, are most vulnerable. |578|: And so on behalf of a grateful one five, on behalf of the beloved community of Watts, thank you for all of your great work in our community. |579|: And God bless you. |580|:  Thank you so much. |581|: And thank you, Mr. Price. |582|: And thank you to all the members that make comments about our beloved Veronica. |583|: And I appreciate, one, hearing from your mom and seeing your family, but also hearing from you about being grounded in values. |584|:  and grounded in the dignity and the value and love for every human being, no matter where we find them or what the situation is. |585|: Members of this council, I think everybody on this council can relate to this. |586|: And one of my first interactions with you, and you only get this when you love the people. |587|: One of my very first interactions with you is we had stood up a new shelter that Hoppix was managing. |588|:  And we were touring the Lhasa director. |589|: And this is a few Lhasa directors ago, so nobody think about the people that you know now. |590|: And while we're touring, it's about six o'clock in the evening in the summer, and a man comes up to the shelter and says, the police just made me move my car that I live in, and they told me to come here and I could get a place to stay. |591|:  And your staff said, well, you know, we have to make this call.", "Embedding": [-0.00035929657, 0.0074858232, 0.011160336, -0.010729227, -0.0015428974, 0.040260788, 0.062392257, 0.039355915, 0.012265041, -0.006392034, 0.008678366, -0.007606235, 0