{"ChunkNum": 27, "StartTime": 4552.976, "EndTime": 4749.303, "Content": "|592|: We have to fill out this paper. |593|: We have, you know, we have a million excuses not to help people in this city and county. |594|: But so we kind of went through those. |595|: And I remember the LASA director said, let me call someone downtown and we can smooth it over and you can stay here tonight. |596|: And that person made a phone call and no one picked up. |597|: And he kind of looked at me and said, well, there's nothing we can do. |598|:  And at the moment he said that, you went into action. |599|: And to this day, I don't know what you did or what papers you moved around or what administrative process you went through, but we got that person in a bed that night. |600|:  Since then, every time we've come to you, you're one of the few people in our entire homelessness establishment, you're one of the few people who starts with how do we get this human being in a bed and safe right away. |601|: No matter what the funding stream is, no matter what the losses this group says or that group says or the other group says,\n|602|:  You're always grounded in believing that no human being should sleep on the street for any reason anywhere in our city. |603|: And so with that type of fire, I know you'll continue to make a contribution and you won't be able to stop yourself from helping our folks. |604|: So again, thank you for all you have done and a great honor to you and your family for everything that you will do. |605|: Mr. Price. |606|: Thank you, Mr. President. |607|:  To our Shiro, I just want to present this as a token of our appreciation, signed by the mayor, every member of the council. |608|: We love you, we honor you, keep up the good work. |609|:  Thank you so much. |610|: All right now we will hear from Council District 7 Councilmember Monica Rodriguez. |611|:  Come on, the whole family.", "Embedding": [-0.0004935247, 0.0068159103, 0.01778462, -0.007983444, -0.0015645745, 0.