{"ChunkNum": 28, "StartTime": 4755.031, "EndTime": 5175.545, "Content": "|612|: All right. |613|:  Good morning, colleagues. |614|: Well, it's a very special morning here in council chambers. |615|: And at this particular juncture, and by the way, it's only for this man that I would actually take hat here today, for the person that we are honoring. |616|: But it's really a tremendous honor to have an opportunity to celebrate the individuals that\n|617|:  really help to ground our community in our cultural history, our traditions, at a time especially when our community is under attack. |618|: And I'm proud to honor today a man who has helped to continue to ground us in tremendous cultural pride,\n|619|:  in so much of what our community represents from the hard work, the spirit, the ganas, the unwavering commitment to being authentically who we are. |620|: And ladies and gentlemen, it's my great honor that today we are recognizing and honoring and celebrating Don Diolardo Lopez. |621|: Please give him a round of applause. |622|:  Don Leonardo Lopez is a leader that has strengthened our communities, inspired generations, helping to make sure that we tell the very important story of our Latino heritage. |623|: Born in La Noria, Durango, Mexico, Don Leonardo was raised with the values of perseverance, dedication, and faith in family. |624|:  When he came to the United States back in the 1960s, he carried those values with him and began working as a dishwasher in Santa Monica. |625|: From those early days, he built a legacy that has touched thousands of lives. |626|: With the love and partnership of his wife, Dona Iris, Leonardo went on to become a pioneer. |627|:  of many Latino-owned businesses. |628|: He founded the beloved restaurants such as El Mariachi, Leonardo's, and Laboon. |629|: These establishments became more than just places to eat. |630|: They became the places where our culture, our music, and our community came alive to celebrate many wonderful occasions. |631|: And most notably,\n|632|:  His stewardship of the Pico Rivera Sports Arena has cemented its status as an international landmark. |633|: Generations have gathered there to celebrate chariadas, escaramuza, concerts, which I had the privilege of being at recently, and the festivals that celebrate and honor and preserve our heritage. |634|:  Pico Rivera has served as the community and was even used as an evacuation and holding area for horses during the most recent January wildfires. |635|: Through his work, Leonardo has created thousands of jobs, empowered entrepreneurs, and provided a platform for cultural celebration. |636|: Right now, given the unconstitutional immigration enforcement that continues to assault our community,\n|637|:  His spaces have created a place where we can continue to be authentically who we are, proudly celebrate our cultural traditions, and it's a reflection. |638|: His story is really a reflection of everything of what it means to be a Latino. |639|: Everything that I believe is our Mexican cultural heritage. |640|: So many of our families can share these same stories. |641|:  We are a community of dedicated, hardworking entrepreneurs that make it work for our families, taking the opportunity that this country gives us every single day to turn nothing into something. |642|: And what he has done is created a magnificent\n|643|:  history here in our communities, not just in the city of Los Angeles, but in Pico Rivera, but it is emanated and rippled in so many parts of our city, our county. |644|: And I am for one very grateful that he had the tenacity and the strength and the entrepreneurial spirit to do everything that he's done. |645|:  When I think about the lives that have been changed, when I think, I mean, you can cite the musicians that have been discovered as a result of you giving them an audience and a platform to perform. |646|: When I think about the jobs and the economic strength that has been created by his spirit, and make no mistake, for anyone that thinks building a business is easy,\n|647|:  Boy, you got another thing coming. |648|: There are so many obstacles that are put before you to create a business, and you have done it. |649|: It seems almost effortlessly, but it's been grounded in great community pride. |650|: And when I think about growing up as a first-generation American of Mexican descent, and I think about how so many of us\n|651|:  have been forced to abandon the language, the music, the storytelling, because in the eras that we were raised in, it wasn't quite celebrated. |652|: And I think about when Linda Ronstadt,\n|653|:  produced canciones de mi padre, how that was an inflection point for our community, and how we continue to just grow and strengthen in our community pride, in our musical traditions. |654|: Those were moments. |655|: And we're in another moment like that today, that we will not redact, retreat. |656|: We will continue to be strong as a community, celebrating our incredible, beautiful culture. |657|: And I'm incredibly grateful. |658|:  to this man, his entire family, that have helped to sustain our community through the celebration of music, of cultural pride, and just a tremendous sense of just love for our community and our culture. |659|: So I just want to say, Don Leonardo, it's been an incredible honor getting to know you, getting to spend time with you and your family, and I really appreciate\n|660|:  and value, not only the friendship, but the incredible work and dedication that each of you exude every day, generations that continue this important legacy. |661|: It gives me such pride to say I'm a Mexican-American and to see how you've built this empire. |662|: And make no mistake, it's an empire. |663|: It's really remarkable and refreshing to know that\n|664|:  You took the opportunity that was afforded you in this country, and you made something of it. |665|: And you did it grounded in being authentically who you are.", "Embedding"