{"ChunkNum": 29, "StartTime": 5175.946, "EndTime": 5493.069, "Content": "|666|: And for that, I'm incredibly grateful and honored to know you, to celebrate you, and give you this well-deserved honor. |667|: And I am joined today by my friend, the former mayor of Huntington Park, and the 41st treasurer of the United States, Rosario Marin, who would like to offer a few words. |668|:  Thank you, Councilmember Rodriguez. |669|: It's an honor to be here on this very spacious occasion, celebrando a Don Leonardo Lopez. |670|: Very fitting, and thank you, Councilmembers and Mr. President of the Council. |671|: Thank you for this opportunity. |672|: You really, really have done something very special here today. |673|: You're doing something that will be\n|674|:  in the memory of the entire family and the community that supports Leonardo. |675|: I have known him for more than 40 years. |676|: And when I was first elected to the city council in Huntington Park back in 1994, Leonardo was there. |677|: Leonardo has always been there. |678|: He has been there for the city, for his family, for his community. |679|:  for all the beautiful traditions that his heritage evokes. |680|: This man represents the very best in all of us. |681|: His hard work, his steadfast commitment to upholding our culture make him, in my book, a real treasure. |682|:  And I know a little bit about treasures. |683|: So I want to thank you. |684|: There's nothing more that I can say that a council member has already said. |685|: But I do want to say to his family, you do have somebody to look up to. |686|: And please continue his wonderful legacy that all of you represent. |687|: Thank you. |688|: Thank you very much. |689|:  And so now, colleagues, it is my great honor to now invite the man that we honor today, helping us. |690|: And I want to thank Councilmember Hernandez, our madrina, for El Grito. |691|: You know, when I think about El Grito and what it represents, it's that moment to remind everyone in our community that that was the cry to fight. |692|:  That was the calling for us to continue to be strong in the face of adversity. |693|: And we will continue to push back. |694|: And I want to thank you, Don Leonardo, for being that example of how we can really be the force of resilience and strength in the wake of adversity. |695|: You are that example. |696|: And it's a reminder to everyone who's feeling down is that we will persevere. |697|:  And so ladies and gentlemen, please help me welcome our honoree today, Don Leonardo Lopez. |698|: Thank you. |699|: Love L.A. Monica, you really made it. |700|: It's been a hard work and I'm very honored to be here. |701|: I thank you very much for the hard work. |702|:  I thank everyone that has been with me and everybody that is here with me today, my family, my beautiful wife, my in-laws, my nieces and my sons and my granddaughters and grandsons. |703|:  Thanks to the city council of this beautiful city of angels. |704|: Thanks, Mr. President. |705|: Thank you very much. |706|: Thanks again, and viva Mexico. |707|: Viva la charrer\u00eda. |708|: Viva. |709|: We love our culture and our music. |710|: We did everything for you guys,\n|711|:  lot of Mexican people that are still there working, and I really want to thank everybody. |712|: I want to introduce my son, Fernando, but he has been with me. |713|: All of my sons are here today. |714|: So thank you very much, City Council of Los Angeles. |715|: Thank you. |716|: Thank you, Monica. |717|:  Thank you for honoring my father and Fiestas Patrias and El Grito. |718|: It's going to be forever in our memory. |719|: I would like to thank the City Council. |720|: Thank you, President. |721|: My mom for all the patience that she's had for my dad to do what he does. |722|: And most importantly, the City of LA. |723|:  Because I think my dad's first love is the city of LA, and then it's the horses. |724|: Because if it wasn't for the city of LA, he wouldn't afford the horses. |725|: So thank you.", "Embedding": [-0.00040752388, -0.009016914, 0.036114737, 0.021526542, -0.0018020249, 0.07348435, 0.024362909, 0.018783903, 0.009196372, 0.004790428, 0.011177597, -0.022451602, 0.004255832, 0.026629651, 0.01766079, 0.008181554, -0.020371413, -0.050175097, -0.0102361115, -0.00029314286, -0.008517273, -0.015869565, 0.079256125, 0.033775903, 0.068129584, -0.0040383125, -0.02405057, 0.0076336693, -0.010576206, 0.015717287, -0.0726753, -0.039565794, 0.0076011308, -0.011792952, -0.0012971029, 0.009559554, 0.010740216, 0.0018639052, 0.023931863, 0.014760195, 0.00920728, 0.01743004, 0.01325241, 0.0077755973, -0.006359598, 0.0022991435, -0.0086399065, 0.033271465, -0.01797348, -0.017673135, 0.00460192, -0.0025254884, -0.033205397, -0.011983385, -0.0026016356, 0.018975144, 0.01589428, -0.009392537, 0.029176563, -0.059094492, 0.014242778, -0.0004583028, -0.0221682, -0.013480463, -0.0035570052, -0.026477579, -0.00088487775, -0.0099399155, 0.00039227578, -0.018625576, -0.023100212, -0.011792507, -0.013151449, -0.0060064285, -0.013923034, -0.0129952915, -0.0016006002, 0.002867877, -0.0227671, 0.0023402113, -0.030845592, 0.012757283, -0.0064048246, 0.013338406, -0.018702328, 0.028336149, 0.021087594, 0.0001417205, 0.0032475102, 0.01076492, -0.0008132642, -0.030535929, -0.017754415, 0.026504748, 0.0016079287, 0.019780356, -0.017215647, -0.025240393, 0.006518937, 0.002017555, -0.007652349, -0.021215474, -0.017281834, 0.00042727226, 0.015665283, -0.018610807, -0.0015057431, -0.009013815, 0.0062974505, 0.013761408, -0.0011362453, 0.0012706846, -0.036327116, -0.01753486, 0.020290928, -0.00982117, 0.012825402, 0.01349187, 0.009152783, -0.055558696, 0.008276133, -0.0008936783, -0.007978206, -0.011684785, -0.00012721817, 0.0003877759, -0.01285875, -0.0061603156, 0.021395817, -0.022814838, -0.016528837, -0.018381601, -0.04392437, 0.008293426, 0.032724213, -0.002425886, -0.0035877877, 0.0071973973, -0.010773897, 0.01297764, 0.008299609, 0.0023428034, 0.002787208, -0