{"ChunkNum": 30, "StartTime": 5493.55, "EndTime": 5760.417, "Content": "|726|: Thank you, dad. |727|: Congratulations. |728|: God bless America, like he says, and viva Mexico. |729|: All right, we got a few members on the queue. |730|: Councilmember Padilla. |731|:  Councilmember Rodriguez, what a great presentation to bring in as we, you know, start the celebration of Latino Hispanic Heritage Month here in the City of Los Angeles. |732|: Don Leonardo, felicidades, felicidades to the entire family. |733|: You know, when I look at this presentation, I see a presentation honoring a family and what a family that's united can accomplish. |734|:  when they're in a place that's so far from their original place from home. |735|: And making an empire by preserving the traditions that we bring from Mexico. |736|: So thank you for all you do. |737|: Thank you for being part of that group of folks that make it so that we are unapologetic about our music, our food, and our presence, and recognizing that we're just next door. |738|:  You know, so as was said right now, you know, God bless America. |739|: Que viva Mexico. |740|: That really is how we've been. |741|:  indoctrinated here, right? |742|: That's the theme. |743|: We always remember Mexico, but at the same time, we know why we came here. |744|: And your family, Don Leonardo Lopez, you guys embody exactly what that means, so congratulations. |745|: Because you're definitely the kind of family that pays it forward, and I appreciate you for all of that. |746|: Thank you. |747|: Thank you so much. |748|: Councilmember Lee. |749|:  Thank you, Mr. President, and thank you, Councillor Rodriguez, for bringing in Don Leonardo. |750|: I can't think of a more fitting person to honour today. |751|: Don Leonardo, you know how I feel about your entire family. |752|: I want to say just thank you for everything you've done to share your culture with our city. |753|: You are another example of what makes this city so incredible. |754|:  You are an icon in the chattel community, but you've also shared so many other beautiful things, the food, the music with all of us, and I just want to say thank you. |755|: But I want you to look around when you see your family. |756|: You are... |757|:  that piece that keeps that family all together. |758|: You don't just ask them to come over and see each other once a year or different things. |759|: You make sure that this family stays together, whether it's your weekend dinners at your house or the different events that you throw together. |760|: I want to say thank you to you, but also to your amazing family. |761|: When you look around at what this family has done, there's so many members of this\n|762|:  family that have done so much for the different communities of the city of Los Angeles. |763|: You have successful businessmen. |764|: You have people who have built things. |765|: You have\n|766|:  a great doctor over there. |767|: And I just want to say, I just want to say thank you so much, Don Leonardo. |768|: Thank you for letting us, you know, sharing those things for us and really, really all your contributions to this great city of ours. |769|: And just want to say thank you for allowing me to be a part of your 50th wedding anniversary where you renewed your vows to your lovely wife, Iris, to the Lopez family. |770|: Thank you very much for everything you all do. |771|:  But thank you Don Leonardo. |772|: Thank you so much members and thank you so much Councilwoman Rodriguez for bringing in the Lopez family and for showing up as you always do. |773|: You are such angels in this city. |774|: LA is not LA without Don Leonardo and the Lopez family and all that you contribute. |775|:  I'm the proud representative of not one but two Leonardo's ballrooms, one of them I can walk to. |776|: And, you know, members in public, I want folks to know what a big deal this is because there was a period there in the late 80s through the early 90s where a lot of businesses, especially ones that did live music, just went away. |777|: They left.", "Embedding": [-0.0004818681, 0.005490585, 0.05379258, -0.007988829, -0.002023985, 0.05097975, 0.023252936, -0.0011550821, 0.011065348, 0.004556016, 0.02670111, -0.020241184, 0.0017184814, 0.012733795, 0.01923301, 0.0147795295, -0.023831062, -0.056899823, -0.026639115, 0.00085144653, -0.009861136, -0.022863915, 0.07706449, 0.03020782, 0.072864875, -0.063914984, -0.02182017, 0.02231897, -0.014587482, -0.005017385, -0.043454185, -0.04290167, 0.008077932, -0.029584017, -0.0010903858, 0.010309946, 0.02546541, -0.003366276, 0.03630362, 0.009237726, 0.015470754, -0.013029106, 0.003395503, 0.010980186, 0.009860641, 0.0037989987, -0.00055146764, 0.020929668, -0.012057875, -0.021773206, 0.003432242, -0.005540444, -0.045699373, -0.005528711, -0.015398414, 0.03670365, 0.019672904, -0.005419043, 0.02218579, -0.029635863, 0.010656874, -0.0024935706, -0.034860507, -0.011857306, -0.0074522453, -0.022079617, 0.0008467597, -0.04493714, 0.0017531536, -0.0026406113, -0.01675027, 0.001965824, -0.038716223, -0.007916757, -0.020193761, -0.007234716, -0.0037947649, -0.0023375705, -0.0037977179, 0.006707751, -0.010127138, 0.00081127475, -0.00025283775, -0.00070201856, -0.022486316, 0.012742307, -0.0042791218, -0.0009985177, -0.02168297, 0.0061744777, -0.0032231156, -0.045545362, -0.010519047, 0.039053537, -0.0059546367, 0.005171723, -0.02425234, -0.016385583, 0.0013368297, 0.0038214945, 0.0012557306, -0.022958148, -0.016558228, -0.023228131, 0.019439284, -0.01970814, -0.0103946235, -0.030460661, 0.0035185, 0.010033242, 0.0073160636, 0.0021732093, -0.0044179475, 0.008056785, 0.014348359, -0.013319492, 0.009707449, 0.012041402, 0.003607738, -0.05838204, 0.008870879, -0.005036268, -0.0015963379, -0.009869689, -0.014283424, -0.011061265, -0.009255107, -0.0141752325, 0.005234944, -0.0071125613, -0.007909375, -0.007367071, -0.031616554, -0.011751574, 0.02112705, -0.006873765, 0.0081148585, -0.005083711, -0.014473654