{"ChunkNum": 31, "StartTime": 5760.903, "EndTime": 5864.428, "Content": "|778|:  And you all never left. |779|: You opened up every weekend to this day. |780|: You opened up every weekend. |781|: The only time I've seen you closed is that weekend where we had those terrible ice rates. |782|:  It's the only time I've seen you and you all were back the next week, ready to go and you had security out and you were doing your thing. |783|: So it's, you know, it's a great, you all are a great example of what it means to be Angelino and what it means to be community members and I was proud to be at your 50th wedding anniversary. |784|: I think my wife's a little bit upset with me because I forgot to mention that you were being honored today. |785|: She probably would have wanted to be here to hug you all and thank you all for treating us like family. |786|:  from the moment that we we met you and interacted with you and\n|787|:  you all both promote your organization and your business and your family, but also the neighborhood. |788|: So when we have a jazz festival and the neighborhood goes to you, you all deliver food to the jazz festival. |789|: When there's a sporting event with young people in the community, you all step up and participate in those events, even for parts of the community that may or may not use your businesses. |790|: So thank you for everything that you've been, and we look forward to\n|791|:  the years when the grandkids take over and we build an even bigger empire and shine a brighter light from here in the city of Los Angeles from the Lopez family. |792|: Thank you all so much. |793|: Councilmember Rodriguez. |794|: Thank you. |795|:  Thank you, Mr. Harris-Dawson. |796|: And I brought up the example of the next generation that is also helping to carry on the tradition. |797|: I'm surprised he didn't show up on a horse, because he generally doesn't like to not be on a horse. |798|: But it's really remarkable.", "Embedding": [-0.00068224146, -0.0037