{"ChunkNum": 41, "StartTime": 7181.997, "EndTime": 7266.073, "Content": "|1012|: I don't know how much time I have. |1013|:  What we've always done as an organizer going door to door meeting with the families is that we are not only how we survive all these attacks, but we're going to survive the current reactionary racist Trump regime and we will win by building a mass powerful movement that relies on the power of the people, not on isolated acts of individuals, okay? |1014|:  Yeah, yeah, no, absolutely. |1015|: The power of the people. |1016|: I've always relied on the moms, the youth in our community. |1017|: Whenever I've been arrested and beat up, many times, you know, they've always supported me to stay out of jail, right? |1018|: So, you know, in wrapping it up, I mentioned that the Mexican-American War, 1848,\n|1019|:  We develop a unique culture, which we're celebrating today, a little bit more Mexican. |1020|: I'm proud of my Mexican roots, but I am Chicano. |1021|: And Chicano has a history in the Southwest. |1022|: We're unique. |1023|: We develop into a distinct people striving for what we call self-determination. |1024|: And we popularize self-determination of oppressed people. |1025|: We popularize it by saying Chicano. |1026|:  So when I say Chicano, everybody would say power. |1027|: And we say raza si, guerra no. |1028|: So, you know, I'm just to wrap it up. |1029|: I keep saying wrap it up, right?", "Embedding": [-0.00040755377, -0.014425374, 0.019370861, -0.032261103, -0.0014102098, 0.0327465, 0.0046011936, 0.01921744, 0.010232754, 0.014378557, 0.033948738, -0.047312353, 0.0040231426, 0.005278606, 0.029759213, 0.0032674395, -0.02969057, 0.011798847, -0.005411817, 0.0008690693, -0.014962185, 0.018435132, 0.07519673, 0.048405506, 0.080806464, -0.040662408, -0.029099362, -0.026222806, -0.0042720367, -0.015120466, -0.03788143, -0.055463653, -0.030266292, -0.010527006, -0.0026093447, 0.006719333, 0.01792381, -0.004994117, 0.033352945, 0.0068505616, -0