{"ChunkNum": 44, "StartTime": 7290.635, "EndTime": 7413.214, "Content": "|1041|: Let's do it. |1042|: Well, yeah, and the young people that I work with, I sit there over at UC ACLU at a big forum. |1043|:  All right as you're doing the photo op Mr.. Montez and and members we got a few speakers on the queue beginning with councilmember mccasker of the 15th district Thank you very much I know Hey growing up in La you know Mexican-American culture Mexican culture so important to all of us and I grew up with this story and\n|1044|:  of the battalion of the San Patricios. |1045|: In the Mexican-American war, a whole bunch of conscripted Irish-Americans or Irish immigrants were fighting on the side of the U.S. against the Mexicans and reached a point where a significant number of them said, we have more in common with them than we have with our bosses. |1046|:  and actually deserted. |1047|: This is a story that we talk about in our family a lot. |1048|: Actually deserted, went over to the Mexican side and fought as the battalion of the San Patricios. |1049|: And I have a giant flag in my office in San Pedro of the battalion of the San Patricios. |1050|: And what's, I wouldn't take time on this except there is really a significant thing for today. |1051|: Now not surprisingly, the San Patricios lost to the Americans and they were hung. |1052|:  as deserters. |1053|: Most of them were hung on September 12th today. |1054|: Today in Mexico City, in the Plaza of San Jacinto, I believe, there is always a celebration on September 12th in honor of the San Patricios. |1055|: We celebrate them two times in Mexico City, St. Patrick's Day and September 12th. |1056|: And so it is appropriate that on our Day of El Grito, and talking about the resistance, I just say that\n|1057|:  Mexican-American culture, Latino culture is special to you, but it should be special to every single one of us. |1058|: So thank you.", "Embedding": [-0.00044813583, -0.023308478, 0.05804801, -0.02305787, -0.