{"ChunkNum": 49, "StartTime": 8199.145, "EndTime": 8298.884, "Content": "|1170|: Mr. City Attorney, Mr. |1171|: Clerk, I believe we're prepared for public comment at this time. |1172|:  Yes, Mr. President, I will go through the brief instructions as members of the public. |1173|: If you are here to provide public comment, please note that the items on the agenda have already had public comment satisfied, so you will have up to one minute for general public comment if you'd like. |1174|:  Keep in mind during general public comment, you still need to speak to something that's within the subject matter jurisdiction of this body. |1175|: We would ask as well that because it looks like there's not a ton of people here for public comment, feel free to line up in any order on your left-hand side of the council chambers. |1176|:  If you see more than five people lined up, I would just ask that you please wait so that we don't create a fire hazard and then we can cycle people through. |1177|: And you can line up in any order. |1178|: You will have one minute total. |1179|: So as soon as you get to the podium, we will start your time. |1180|: And if you require assistance or have an accommodation request, please let the sergeants know. |1181|: Thank you. |1182|:  So again, to repeat, we are not going to call names, but you can line up. |1183|: If you see more than five people on the left-hand side of council chambers, I would ask that you please just wait until the line gets a little bit smaller. |1184|: We're going to start with the woman with the handheld mic. |1185|: Good morning. |1186|: You have one minute. |1187|: Go ahead. |1188|: Before we start our time, let's make sure it's working. |1189|: Can you hear me? |1190|:  I think so. |1191|: Yes, we can. |1192|: Go ahead. |1193|: You have one minute.", "Embedding": [-0.000249576, -0.06383295, -0.041539047, 0.03195422, -0.000969517, 0.012519787, 0.07618421, -0.027311062, -0.0005513814, 0.0056528407, 0.023166068, 0.01307422