{"ChunkNum": 57, "StartTime": 8580.175, "EndTime": 8791.971, "Content": "|1251|:  I'm Dr. Sam Davidson, and I volunteer with Equal Vote. |1252|: I recently completed my PhD in bioengineering at Caltech, and now I'm planning to move from Pasadena to LA. |1253|: I endorse STAR voting, which fully eliminates the spoiler effect. |1254|: Statistical modeling shows that STAR produces the most accurate elections. |1255|:  Simulations run by a statistician from Harvard show that under the current top two system, the candidate who best represents as many voters as possible will be elected 90% of the time, whereas rank choice is better, electing the ideal winner roughly 93% of the time, and star is even better than that, electing the ideal winner 98% of the time. |1256|:  These figures were published in a peer-reviewed journal article which can be found at equal.vote.accuracy alongside simulations developed independently by UC Berkeley computer science PhD and a Cornell University professor. |1257|: LA now has a chance to become the world leader in electoral accuracy by adopting star voting before any other city. |1258|: Thank you. |1259|:  Okay, so as usual, we're making public participation as difficult and little as possible, going through like extended period of presentations, you know, cutting off\n|1260|:  All preventing the public from speaking on agenda items because they had a hearing earlier, even though that was the committee vote, not the full council vote. |1261|: And many of these members of this council have never heard public comment on any of the agenda items because it was in committees that they weren't on. |1262|: Which means that they didn't get a full public hearing. |1263|: They didn't get a hearing for every member of this council. |1264|:  So you're preventing people from speaking on these items because, again, you don't want to sit here and learn about all the terrible stuff about the agenda items because you're trying to limit public participation. |1265|: Just like call and comment that you've made zero statement on why that was eliminated. |1266|: Why is there no call and comment anymore? |1267|: Fire Jim McDonald, cancel the Olympics, and what's going on outside? |1268|: It's like a mess out there. |1269|:  I just wanted to say thank you to Carlos Montes for advocating for an end to aid to Israel. |1270|: He probably didn't know how many Zionists he was speaking to. |1271|: And I wonder if he's aware how many of you voted yes on adopting the IHRI death initiative antisemitism that renders any criticism of Israel hate speech. |1272|: So hopefully you guys don't try to incriminate him for what you would consider hate speech. |1273|:  Nithya Brahmin is the chair, whoa, of the homelessness committee, whoa, yeah. |1274|: But I don't think she really does care, no. |1275|: For the unhoused in the city, no way. |1276|: LA can raise concerns. |1277|: She looked them in the eye. |1278|: They asked for repairs at the Mayfair, and she told them a lie. |1279|: Mayfair hotel elevators, how long have they been broken down? |1280|: Mayfair hotel elevators, she lied when she said that they're working now. |1281|:  Nithya why did you say those elevators were fixed when they still have cones in front of them and residents can't get to their apartments? |1282|:  That's not cool. |1283|: I guess we want to get the public comment, right? |1284|: Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah. |1285|: Damn, my time is running and he's giving me instructions. |1286|: Hold on just a second. |1287|: Thank you, thank you.", "Embedding": [-0.0003084811, 0.05046124, -0.018190209, 0.03897345, -0.0015489364, 0.057407334, 0.042956572, -0.027392518, 8.3415085e-05, -0.0035316183, 0.062519036, 0.015397254, 0.005420445, -0.030683879, -0.045565814, -0.019978732, 0.00021029986, 0.05219133, 0.039711006, -0.0079086125, -0.0051711015, 0.046647213, 0.07524958, 0.012957687, -0.007619861, -0.032111496, -0.0338889, -0.047214035, -0.013060048, -0.0062982575, -0.05757812, -0.02