{"ChunkNum": 58, "StartTime": 8792.352, "EndTime": 8943.075, "Content": "|1288|: Go ahead, you have one minute. |1289|: I noticed that Marquis Harris Dawson waited until the black community activist Veronica left today before he told there was a black lady here in a scooter and a chair. |1290|:  And she was pulled up here, and he waited until the black community activists left before he told her, nah, you gotta put that chair in the back, and then you gotta walk over here and sit in the pew. |1291|: You can't just be right here on your scooter. |1292|: So that was fucked up. |1293|: And there wasn't hardly anybody here. |1294|: There was maybe a dozen and a half people here, and nobody be walking through that spot. |1295|:  That's kind of bullshit. |1296|: I don't like that shit. |1297|: You know, black people always take care of me. |1298|: I don't like when I see, especially other black people, like, in positions of power, tear down black people in the public, or like, make their life unnecessarily inconvenient. |1299|: I know Marquis has done a lot of good work, and he's very strategic. |1300|:  You got to watch out for that. |1301|: He's a very tactical person, and he does everything with an agenda in mind. |1302|: I respect that to a degree. |1303|: I respect the skill, but I got to call it out. |1304|: And we got to come together, y'all. |1305|: A lot of people that we don't agree with, we won't have to come together and resist even this government, because they've taken away our public spaces and our public comment, little by little. |1306|: And they don't really care about trans people. |1307|: They don't care about black people. |1308|: Your time is expired. |1309|: I need you to vacate the podium so we can move on to the next speaker. |1310|:  Speaker, you are now disrupting this meeting as we cannot continue the public comment. |1311|: This is your first and only formal warning. |1312|: Good morning. |1313|: I'm sorry, good afternoon. |1314|: You have one minute, go ahead. |1315|: Good morning, Council. |1316|: My name is Akile. |1317|: I'm with Black Lives Matters LA, and I came here to commend, to celebrate, and be with my friend, Carlos Montes. |1318|: Carlos has demonstrated real solidarity, not just\n|1319|:  implied solidarity, and his work with CSO has supported Black Lives Matters ever since we got started. |1320|: So I'm here today, one, to acknowledge him, two, to celebrate him, and three, to thank him. |1321|: Thank you so much, Carlos. |1322|: We are glad to call you a friend. |1323|: We're glad to call you a Conrad, and this is well deserved. |1324|: Thank you. |1325|: Good afternoon. |1326|: Go ahead. |1327|: You have one minute. |1328|:  General public comment. |1329|: Public, here we go. |1330|: Public, when you hire clowns, you get a circus. |1331|: Sleazy Marqueezy Dawson and the rest of these clowns, again, have absolutely zero items on today's agenda. |1332|: None.", "Embedding": [-0.00041438776, -0.053824298, -0.020542482, -0.022857156, -0.0015424899, 0.045580134, 0.019017225, -0.010252034, 0.016093578, -0.028689453, 0.048905905, 0.032821566, 0.0042564045, -0.0057236613, -0.006501697, 0.0016908447, 0.0072261305, 0.013780565, 0.026576655, -5.7533958e-05, -0.011228164, -0.00038880343, 0.09616003, 0.0068650963, 0.066368856, -0.008230328, -0.029695444, -0.023065044, 0.012318391, 0.00421164, -0.05913192, -0.08781617, -0.0004421912, -0.01668917, -8.68179e-05, 0.009173787, 0.00888224, 0.0018614156, 0.017014304, 0.01938102, 0.015781906, 0.005800311, 0.0030505005, 0.0072458084, 0.007068925, -0.0061532953, -0.0025193004, 0.016766464, -0.0070095253, -0.024832537, 0.0029121952, 0.0069995034, 0.001964256, -0.0143569335, 0.006896004, 0.017636376, 0.020314528, -0.0007232981, 0.021953475, -0.01703476, 0.009120974, 0.0025579857, -0.008643212, -0.01134189, -0.008049465, -0.025103265, -0.02080476, 0.005090038, -0.006918002, 0.00083083374, -0.035594594, -0.0110048605, -0.014252758, -0.010953069, 0.023470247, -0.014