{"ChunkNum": 65, "StartTime": 9054.923, "EndTime": 9251.942, "Content": "|1359|: You have one minute. |1360|: The Brown Act does not allow you to discuss general public comments at meetings, but it does allow you to respond to the public's concerns via email or by issuing your own statements. |1361|: So please explain why you don't think we're entitled to the highest level of police oversight. |1362|: The governor won't step on the toes of local officials, so it really is your responsibility to request it. |1363|:  Secondly, the city attorney always asks people to send in written comments, and I'd actually prefer to do that, but the instructions do not include the file numbers necessary to read or write general public comments like 25-0000-S9. |1364|: So only people who've asked the city clerk for that information have had the ability to read general comments. |1365|: For anyone else, written general public comments effectively don't exist. |1366|:  Good afternoon, you have one minute, go ahead. |1367|: All your evil upset the baby, see that? |1368|: So anyway, while I was here, Eunice Hernandez, while standing in front of a cop, turns her head and tells me to fuck off. |1369|:  So you see, when she does that, she's a government official in front of a police officer. |1370|: I can't say anything to respond to that. |1371|: She's putting me in fear and coercion and violation of federal and state law. |1372|: So you know, I haven't been coming around a lot. |1373|: Something's coming to this building. |1374|:  Something's coming, man. |1375|: You can just smell the fear in this fucking air. |1376|: Cops all over the place, informants all over the fucking place. |1377|: There's so much activity. |1378|: They've got 39 new agents that came out of state last week to come into that building. |1379|: So they're not here for ICE. |1380|: They're here for you. |1381|: Finally, I'm going to get my $10,000. |1382|: Have a good weekend, nigga. |1383|:  It's your time, please exit. |1384|: That's your time. |1385|: Mr. Spindler, you're no longer allowed to speak because your time has expired. |1386|: This is your first and only warning for disrupting the meeting, for not making the podium, and we cannot continue the public comment. |1387|: Next speaker. |1388|: Good afternoon, speaker. |1389|: Next speaker. |1390|: You have one minute. |1391|: All right, good morning. |1392|: It's the first time I've ever been last. |1393|: These are force multipliers. |1394|:  details about my proposition with my citizenship. |1395|: Two five-year tax plans and at the end of ten years you get an application for naturalization because you require all the prerequisites of the current immigration plan and the competing interests should come to a satisfactory conclusion and\n|1396|:  You get your citizenship, and you're off the money. |1397|: Pay for it. |1398|: We're getting out now. |1399|: $5,000 for 10 years, now we know you're going to obey the tax laws, something you never had to do before. |1400|: Hello.", "Embedding": [-0.00031309784, -0.013357285, -0.028391354, 0.009263682, -0.0011247125, 0.028898677, 0.062971845, -0.024665216, 0.012920107, 0.00041667305, 0.020899363, 0.01625258, 0.0044478844, 0.044029977, -0.011180548, -0.020245004, 0.035742503, 0.057596512, 0.006330987, -0.0030524465, -0.007332054, 0.009472277, 0.1047825, 0.0007659232, 0.028283728, -0.00030707222, -0.02487965, -0.00648722, -0.008615503, 0.002732895, -0.04874482, -0.045816716, -0.005020745, -0.007562753, 0.0008278255, -0.008747355, 0.02719981, 0.004563687, -0.003245211, 0.0067179427, -0.0011929432, 0.008054907, 0.026387095, 0.008972327, 0.004083147, 0.0120064225, 0.0014078593, 0.03333046, -0.037628178, -0.031157108, 0.004499239, 0.0018088343, -0.0056998516, -0.00912499, -0.0063283676, -0.0084896665, 0.0054568993, -0.0008089454, -0.012984358, -0.0122318575, -0.0017978456, 0.011076097, 0.035433505, -0.011742315, -0.006933143, -0.030048357, -0.009168628, -0.018796828, -0.016444543, -0.