{"ChunkNum": 74, "StartTime": 9523.765, "EndTime": 9808.71, "Content": "|1465|: Thank you, Mr. Price. |1466|: Any other announcements, members? |1467|: Mr. Nazarian? |1468|:  Thank you Council President for allowing the opportunity to make the announcement from the podium. |1469|:  In the continued theme of resistance that we've all been discussing today, I wanted to ask all of you to join us today as we honor the memory of Massa Amini. |1470|: On September 13, 2022, Massa Amini was arrested in Tehran by Iran's morality police for nothing more than the way she wore her hair. |1471|: Three days later, she was dead in a hospital. |1472|:  Her life was cut short at 22 years old by the physical trauma inflicted on her while in custody of the morality police. |1473|: Her story is not a rare occurrence, unfortunately. |1474|: For the last two generations, women in Iran have been told how to live, how to dress, and how to behave under the threat of violence and punishment. |1475|:  This is a system that denies women agency over their bodies, their choices, and their futures. |1476|: Masa Amini's death ignited a movement. |1477|: Her name has become a battle cry, not only in Iran, but across the globe. |1478|: Women, life, freedom, those three words have echoed from the streets of Tehran to the capitals of the world. |1479|:  Women under oppression have risked everything, removing their head scarves, cutting their hair, standing shoulder to shoulder to demand recognition as human beings. |1480|: They stood bravely in the face of brutality, fueled by the truth that no regime is able to silence the voice of women. |1481|: The power of courage and resistance shines through the movement. |1482|: It reminds us that dignity and equality are forever worth fighting for. |1483|:  Today, we speak her name to keep her spirit alive, to stand with the women of Iran and with women everywhere who face discrimination and violence. |1484|: Massa Amini should still be alive today. |1485|: Let her memory be a call to action, and I ask all of us to stand in a moment of silence, please. |1486|:  Thank you all very much. |1487|: Today I'm joined with many community members that I'd like to, because no one's gonna be speaking, I'd like to just offer a moment to mention everyone. |1488|: Joining us today are Ali Bozorgme, Sasan Arani, Jimmy Delshad, Farzan Delju, Asal Pahlavan,\n|1489|:  Nilufar Mansouri, Fred Minegar, Ali Emadi, Morteza Bargeshche, John Erdalan, Dr. Miriam Azerbaijani and Amir Tabakh, who couldn't be here with us, but helped with organizing this event as well, Manali Rashidan and Mike Aghili. |1490|:  I'd also like to take this moment and recognize three individuals. |1491|: Ms. Manali Rashidan, who's a biologist with LADWP. |1492|: I want to present her with a certificate of the Masa Amini Day. |1493|:  I'd also like to present to Jahan Ardalan a certificate for recognizing his work for establishing this day when a year ago he joined council member Bob Blumenfield to establish this day. |1494|: Thank you for your work and I'd like to ask the councilman to join us also for the photo. |1495|:  And last but not least, I'd like to recognize Farzan Delju for making the film documenting the last 10 days of Massa's life. |1496|: Thank you all for this opportunity.", "Embedding": [-0.00010655196, 0.009834546, 0.018167313, -0.017730553, -0.00011674875, 0.06049194, -0.018249156, 0.04993653, 0.019842561, -0.024593037, 0.0009347805, -0.013601787, 0.008421537, -0.038806546, 0.007846313, -0.01711262, -0.033225663, -0.046477925, 0.023026874, -0.004762621, -0.01060398, 0.025945883, 0.071433984, -0.018696675, 0.050343815, -0.025340855, -0.025428098, 0.0030255662, 0.031271666, 0.018857617, -0.040942844, -0.027890133, -0.006616891, 0.026942108, 0.0020339414, -0.010233941, -0.016304465, -0.0051400205, -0.006476917, 0.018515777, -0.018167034, -0.02229152, -0.0068590785, -0.004359664, 0.01807859, -0.052206907, -0.0050063143, -0.0027233078, 0.010809633, -0.03209