{"ChunkNum": 79, "StartTime": 10194.409, "EndTime": 10435.686, "Content": "|1546|: 89 is a good life. |1547|: It's a full tenor of years, but we didn't lose Mr. Knight because of old age or because of sickness. |1548|: We lost him because of gun violence. |1549|:  And so I point that out because the scourge of gun violence visits all of us, unfortunately, what station in life you're in. |1550|: You think if I make it to 70 or 60, I'm safe from gun violence in this environment that we have. |1551|: And here Mr. Knight was on the doorstep of 90 years old. |1552|:  And we lose him and mourn him because of the scourge of the gun violence and the availability of guns, the ready availability of guns to frankly people who should not have them. |1553|: And so with that, I ask this council and recognize his family and community and ask that the entire city adjourn in the memory of Mr. Robert Knight. |1554|:  All right, Mr. Nazarian. |1555|: Thank you, Council President. |1556|: Colleagues, I rise today to honor the memory of Houshmand Arely. |1557|:  In honoring him, we celebrate a life devoted to beauty, to art, to the sublime, and to the deep, resonant power of music and memory. |1558|: Born in 1937 in the historic city of Isfahan in Iran, Houshmand began a journey that would shape the course of Persian music and touch the hearts of the world. |1559|:  By the age of 13, Houshmand was studying with the great master Taj Esfahani, a revered figure in Iranian classical music. |1560|: Through performances at Radio Esfahan and with the Esfahan Students Orchestra, Houshmand's voice became a cherished presence at cultural and academic events throughout the city. |1561|:  At the inauguration of the Iranian National Television, Houshmand was invited to perform with the prestigious National Orchestra. |1562|: His collaborations with the composers and instrumentalists during this time helped shape the soundscape of an era. |1563|: His work earned him a UNESCO scholarship, allowing him to travel to the United Kingdom, where he expanded his artistic reach and cultural understanding. |1564|:  In 1977, as Iran stood on the brink of cataclysmic change, Hushmand made the difficult decision to move to the United States, but he never left his music behind. |1565|: He brought with him the soul of Iran, preserved in every note, every performance. |1566|: Here he continued to sing, not just with his voice, but with his heart, his history, and his hope. |1567|:  Houshmand Aghili was more than a vocalist, he was a messenger of memories. |1568|: His music was filled with the essence of Persian poetry, emotion, and longing. |1569|: Through his voice, generations found connection to their homeland, to their language, and to their roots. |1570|: He lives behind a loving family, his son, Mike Aghili, his daughter, Mae Aghili, and his grandson, Cameron Houshmasbi. |1571|:  who carry his name and his spirit. |1572|: Let us remember Houshmand Aghili with gratitude for the songs he gave us, the beauty he shared, and the soul he poured into every note. |1573|: He may no longer walk among us, but his voice, his legacy, will forever echo in our hearts. |1574|: Thank you, colleagues. |1575|: Thank you so much, Mr. Nazarian. |1576|: Any other adjourning motions? |1577|: All right, with that, we are adjourned. |1578|: Thank you so much, everybody. ", "Embedding": [-0.00045671104, -0.008794969, 0.011239319, -0.049639944, -0.0016044748, 0.021586088, 0.041224293, 0.016658837, 0.01015114, -0.041049402, -0.016234634, 0.0049653323, 0.0009916587, -0.018047843, 0.04553832, -0.016353711, 0.005360038, -0.05700197, -0.0004980199, -0.0014433184, -0.0115848845, 0.02890417, 0.049178317, 0.017787779, 0.088948354, 0.006261277, -0.025582282, -0.01963018, 0.017355764, 0.05570746, -0.023474406, -0.044041295, -0.0014615955, 0.00044660375, -0.0009635846, 0.020037193, 0.008446194, 0.00084069086, -0.0036232676, 0.028000398, -0.024865884, 0.019775413, -0.0067076567, 0.005053808, -0.014778976, -0.